Mignon du Preez of South Africa bats during the 2016 International ODI Womens cricket match between South Africa and New Zealand at Boland Park, Paarl on 24 October 2016. JOHANNESBURG - Mignon du Preez has retired from One-Day International and Test cricket with immediate effect. The Proteas star says her decision comes as the South African women's game is in a healthy state. The batter says she wants to focus on the T20 format. She also wants to spend more time with family. Du Preez captained the squad 46 times between 2011 and 2016, winning 24 of those matches.